 # Documentation Guidelines

## Framework Documentation
Use knowledge of:
- Framework in ./packages/framework/src/*
- CLI in ./packages/framework/cli.mjs
- Plugins in ./packages/plugins/**/*
- Documentation site in ./apps/docs
- Vite
- (p)npm
- TypeScript
- Starlight
- Astro
- Tailwind
- MDX

## Documentation Structure
- Organize documentation by feature and functionality
- Provide clear examples and use cases
- Include API references and type definitions
- Document performance considerations and best practices

## Code Documentation
- Use clear and consistent commenting style
- Document complex algorithms and business logic
- Include performance implications in documentation
- Maintain up-to-date API documentation

## Technical Writing
- Write clear, concise documentation
- Include code examples and snippets
- Document edge cases and limitations
- Keep documentation in sync with code changes

## Documentation site
- Uses Astro Starlight
- Remember to update ./apps/docs/astro.config.mjs when adding new pages
- Use existing content in ./apps/docs/src/content/docs/fundamentals/**/*.mdx when adding new documentation files and updating existing files.
